strnlght@netcom.com (David Sternlight) writes:

>(I specifically exempt from the above those, with whom I disagree,
>whose consistent position is against any invention protection
>and who think all software and cryptography ought to be both
>universally available and free. I understand that position,
>but think it both ethically wrong and practically unrealistic.)

You are lumping two different groups of people.  The GNU people
think that software should be free.  I merely believe that patents
are unethical, but have no problem with charging for software.
Basically, I believe that all transactions should be voluntary.
Patents don't fit this position.
